01/11/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- Former opposition Socialist Party (SP) lawmaker Vangjel Tavo announced on Saturday (October 30th) that he is joining the rival Socialist Movement for Integration (SMI), a member of the ruling coalition. "I join my old friends at the SMI to defend my leftist ideas, the interests of my electorate," Tavo told a press conference alongside SMI leader Ilir Meta. With Tavo, the ruling majority will have 74 members in the 140-seat parliament. (Top Channel, Shekulli, Lajmifundit, Top News, VoA - 31/10/10)
